  "body": "When closing my Nethermind node today I caught this. It was 'grey' not 'cyan' like the normal logs.\r\n\r\n```\r\nFatal error. System.AccessViolationException: Attempted to read or write protected memory. This is often an indication that other memory is corrupt.\r\n   at RocksDbSharp.Native.rocksdb_get(IntPtr, IntPtr, Byte[], Int64, IntPtr ByRef, RocksDbSharp.ColumnFamilyHandle)\r\n   at RocksDbSharp.Native.rocksdb_get(IntPtr, IntPtr, Byte[], Int64, RocksDbSharp.ColumnFamilyHandle)\r\n   at Nethermind.Db.Rocks.DbOnTheRocks.KeyExists(Byte[])\r\n   at Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncFeed.AddNode(Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncItem, DependentItem, System.String, Boolean)\r\n   at Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncFeed.HandleTrieNode(Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncItem, Byte[], Int32 ByRef)\r\n   at Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncFeed.HandleResponse(Nethermind.Synchronization.FastSync.StateSyncBatch)\r\n   at Nethermind.Synchronization.ParallelSync.SyncDispatcher`1+<>c__DisplayClass18_0[[System.__Canon, System.Private.CoreLib, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=7cec85d7bea7798e]].<Start>b__1(System.Threading.Tasks.Task)\r\n   at System.Threading.ExecutionContext.RunFromThreadPoolDispatchLoop(System.Threading.Thread, System.Threading.ExecutionContext, System.Threading.ContextCallback, System.Object)\r\n   at System.Threading.Tasks.Task.ExecuteWithThreadLocal(System.Threading.Tasks.Task ByRef, System.Threading.Thread)\r\n   at System.Threading.ThreadPoolWorkQueue.Dispatch()\r\n```",
